===Intransitive verb===
'''to crab''' ('''crabs''', '''crabbing''', '''crabbed''')

#To fish for crabs.
#To complain.
#(''by analogy with the movement of a crab'') Of an aircraft, such as a glider, to move sideways.

===Transitive verb===
'''to crab''' ('''crabs''', '''crabbing''', '''crabbed''')

#(''by analogy with the movement of a crab'') To navigate (an aircraft, e.g., a glider) sideways against an air current in order to maintain a straight-line course.
#(''rare'') To [[back out of]] something.<!--transitive or intransitive?-->

